# Article Outline Skill

## Purpose

Create a clear and logical outline for an article
before writing any full paragraphs.

This skill is meant to ensure that content
is structured before execution.

---

## When to Use

Use this skill when:
- The user asks to write an article or guide
- The topic is broad or complex
- Structure matters more than speed

---

## How to Execute

1. Clarify the goal of the article
2. Identify the intended audience (use profiles if available)
3. Propose a logical sequence of sections
4. Keep section titles clear and descriptive
5. Avoid writing full paragraphs unless explicitly requested

---

## Output Format

- Use a numbered or hierarchical list
- Include short descriptions per section
- Keep the outline concise and easy to revise
